{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review — criterion T1 (prior-art / novel-architecture justification): PASS, no findings.\n\nAffirmations:\n- T1(a) prior art considered: the plan is explicitly grounded in the retired prior art rather than reinventing it — it names the exact prior producer (bespoke `orchestrator.run_review`) and the precise prior contract it reconstructs (db7b AC5: `coverage['metrics']` = det_ms / llm_ms / total_ms / llm_calls / claim_path). The AC pins the equivalence (\"equivalent to the retired run_review telemetry\").\n- T1(b) no novel architecture: this is a reconstruction of a known, previously-shipped contract over the existing workflow recorder, not a new pattern/integration/dependency — no novel-architecture bright-line fires, so no prior-art search is owed.\n- T1(c) capability assertion resolved: the load-bearing assertion that the metrics are \"captured from the workflow run (recorder step timings / the batch_plan coverage)\" names a concrete, existing source mechanism (per-step recorder timings), so it is not an unverified \"library supports X\" claim."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782545717012182001,"uuid":"35edf9e0-0fa8-4ba7-a129-17df1fdd17fa"}